            "answer_text": "Well, the social recognition of them changed in these 60 years. Let me explain how it changed. As you know, Geisha is woman entertainer provide traditional dance and music in traditional style small party. That is not very expensive. Some people would like to be patron of specific Geisha. At that point, it going to be very expensive. Famous example of such Geisha is Tsuji Wako. She became intimate wife of fomer prime minister , Kakuei Tanaka at age of 20 when Tanaka was 28, and had two children later. Kakuei Tanaka - Wikipedia (Kakuei Tanaka - Wikipedia) She of coure perfectly perform her role for Tanaka, never present her existencn in the public and provided peaceful rest for Tanaka. Tanaka also responded to her support. He gave 10000 square feet house for her and gave 10,000,000yen per year, roughly million dollor in todays value. I do not think she is frowned. And I probably believe her influence is not just provide rest. In Japanese history, there were many wemen who contributed lot on polytics. Because Tanaka wanted her, she must be super smart lady capable to help Tanaka in his shadow. Well, it is not public at that time but some people knew and now it is well known. But it is probably the last example I know. And today, many Geishas just provide performance only. So you should not misunderstand their business. Why Geisha like Wako is not popular today. There is no specific law to inhibit it immediately. You may not have dual wife but imetiat wife, if your wife agreed. Japanese society and family had changed. And more importantly, Japanese society request women to act more independent and productive. I pointed out that Geisha like Wako is kind of super lady. Such lady has many opportunity today. That change can't co exist with old style life of Geisha. Instead, we see them today. Enjoy.  And another iconic example of Japanese women today is Tanaka's daughter, Makiko Tanaka. Makiko Tanaka - Wikipedia She served as minister of Japan s