            "answer_text": "No. They are hostesses. They can do traditional dances, play the shamisen, compose poetry and indulge in refined repartee. They have to start quite young as Maiko, apprentices, and it\u2019s hard work. Not many girls are interested in becoming Geisha these days and few can appreciate what they have to offer but they aren\u2019t prostitutes, if that\u2019s what the question is driving at. Some of them are supported financially by patrons, some of whom they have physical relationships with and some of whom they don\u2019s. \u201cInstant Geisha\u201d are somewhat frowned on by real Geishas. There are agencies in Kyoto which do the Geisha Experience. They\u2019ll put a kimono on a girl, do her hair and the make-up and turn her loose on the streets for a day, but she won\u2019t know how to walk properly in a kimono and geta, or get into a taxi, will smoke cigarettes, will fool with her mobile phone, flirt and behave inelegantly and the real Geishas hate this because it gives them a bad reputation. ",
